Aligned models like OpenAI's ChatGPT and Google's PaLM-2 prioritize ethical behavior with criteria such as helpfulness, honesty, and harmlessness. In contrast, Uncensored models like FraudGPT and WormGPT lack alignment safeguards, potentially creating harmful content. PoisonGPT spreads false information intentionally. Vector databases have gained popularity due to generative AI, storing vector embeddings for efficient retrieval. Large language models use embeddings to understand language. Vector databases support distance metrics like Euclidean distance, cosine similarity, and dot product. Indexing methods like LSH, tree-based, and graph-based improve search efficiency. Compression techniques like PQ reduce memory footprint while retaining data structure.
